caption: We found this church accidentally while strolling in the area. It has beautiful architecture, both exterior and interior. The church has a quiet ambiance, and we spent a while there to take a break and recharge our energy before continuing our adventure in the beautiful city of Paris.

We were Lucky because we had our apartment right next to the Basilika Ste-Clotilde. The Basilika is a really nice and very big church in Paris next to Square Samuel Rousseau. The church has a lot of small but very nice windows and sculptures and looks very good day and night.

Beautiful basilica! Quiet, peaceful, and filled with interesting history. Decapitations, relics, frescos, statues, and chapels. Everything a believer can ask for! A great place to pray, meditate and lose one self in the details, symbolisms, and significance of this house of God.
Beautiful and exquisitely detailed Basilica church, with amazingly detailed gothic style on the exteriors.
Stumbled across Sainte-Clotilde while walking through Paris. Stop in and say a prayer.
An overlooked beautiful gemstone in a city blessed with so many! Worth a long visit.
Beautiful church. Free to enter. Do so respectfully.

Gorgeous stained glass windows. Beautiful side alters, some with mild water damage. Very beautiful stone carved stations of the Cross. Worth a visit. Small park opposite the front of the church is nice for a picnic.

We came across it while wandering around the city center of Sainte-Clotilde de Paris. On the one hand, what caught our attention about this imposing Catholic church was the children playing in its garden. Since we were in the summer months, the chirping sounds of children playing water games were spreading. Since I was pregnant at that time, we found this very cute. On the other hand, this magnificent building, which suddenly appeared before you while walking between the streets, really added a great identity to the street where it is located. We also liked the fact that small gardens such as rooftops, terraces or small balconies were designed in many suitable areas of the buildings in some streets in the area where the church is located.
What a beautiful church. Amazing to see the indoor architecture. Purely magic. I have seen other beautiful churches in Paris but this is one my favorite.
Beautiful Basilla. It's less crowded and you can have a moment of silence in this peaceful place
Spooky find right before Halloween ðŸŽƒ â€¦
Beautiful historic church. Open to the public. Historical information posted throughout the church in French,  English and Chinese.
Amazingly beautiful church.
An amazing Basilica, relatively new (- 180 years). Amazing architecture and great state of conservation.
We were passing by and heard live music playing went inside, we had a live concert in the first row of amazing orchestral music.
Attended a tribute to CÃ©sar Franck here and thoroughly enjoyed it. Hearing the church organ play was exceptional.
Beautiful church in Paris, host of famous organist Jean Langlais. Check out the regular concerts!
Very beautiful structure to see! Must.
Great example of Gothic style basilica with two twin towers.
Lovely church in the left bank of Paris
Such a beautiful church.   We went in and the organist was rehearsing.  Just amazing sound. The chapels are beautiful as is the stained glass.
Wonderful neo- gothic church with  splendid twin towers in calm neighbourhood.
A beautiful church with many points of interest without the huge crowds. And the park outside has a rabbit.

Stumbled across this church by accident late at night - the doors were open, and inside musicians and choir were performing. Very talented people, welcoming old church (though I'm not at all religious).

A large, restful church just off Les Invalides, with a pleasant garden in front.  Worth trying to catch one of the recitals on their fabulous and world-famous organ. The terrasse of the chic bistro Le Basilic alongside is a true hidden gem of this area (though it's expensive...).

A beautiful gothic church hidden between Parisian houses in the 7th arrondissement. I recommend it for somewhat offbeat visits of Paris. The area is very calm and safe also the church is lighted beautifully in the evening.

Charming sun light through stained glass windows in the late afternoons, quiet and hiden , we were alone almost all time visiting! You can see and understand the logic of gothic arhitecture in such a moment in the right place, the light is sacro and how could feel medieval chridtians the holly spirit in the church in the same way!
This beautiful church was sadly closed when we visited so we didn't get to see it from inside. There are few benches in the courtyard to enjoy a coffee overlooking the church.
Beautiful French Gothic Roman Catholic Basilica with stunning two Towers . This stunning building is the main feature of Samuel Rousseau Square in Paris. Worth exploring.
Outstanding Basilique Saint-Clothilde was the wife of Clovis She was a princess who became Ã  Saint
Beautiful & hidden in plain sight! Not on map unless you enter name Rivals Notre Dame for experience. Not as large but worth the trek. Near Rodin & Invalides
Beautiful church, the view from our hotel Westin Vendome by Tuileries Garden.
Amazing cathedral
Wonderful Catholic Church & square. Come to the mass on Sundays. This the most peaceful place in most of the world I know.
I have seen the spires from Rue Cler  and we just happened to walk by on our way back from the Pantheon.   Beautiful.
One of the lightest churches of Paris... Adds to the ambience... Great organ too worth visiting
If you can't visit Notre Dame, this place will fulfill your desire.
